cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper addresses the challenge of 3D human pose estimation from a single color image using Convolutional Networks (ConvNets). 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes an end-to-end learning paradigm for the task. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with the representation of 3D pose and employs a fine discretization of the 3D space around the subject. 
4. cs.GR (Graphics) is a possible category as the paper deals with the estimation of 3D human pose from a single image, which is relevant to computer graphics applications. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) is another possible category as the paper deals with the estimation of 3D human pose, which is relevant to robotics applications such as human-robot interaction and motion planning.
